{"metadata":{"symbolKind":"class","roleHeading":"Class","title":"MultipleSizeSemanticTokens","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MultipleSizeSemanticTokens"}],"modules":[{"name":"OUDSTokensSemantic"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MultipleSizeSemanticTokens","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"c:@M@OUDSTokensSemantic@objc(cs)MultipleSizeSemanticTokens","role":"symbol"},"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/multiplesizesemantictokens"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Initializers","generated":true,"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleSizeSemanticTokens\/init(_:)","doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleSizeSemanticTokens\/init(compact:regular:)"]},{"anchor":"Instance-Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleSizeSemanticTokens\/compact","doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleSizeSemanticTokens\/regular"],"title":"Instance Properties","generated":true},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleSizeSemanticTokens\/dimension(for:)","doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleSizeSemanticTokens\/isEqual(_:)"],"generated":true,"title":"Instance Methods","anchor":"Instance-Methods"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"MultipleSizeSemanticTokens","kind":"identifier"}]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"code":["        \/\/ Assuming in Figma with have a size semantic token sizeIconWithHeadingXLargeTall,","        \/\/ two semantic size tokens will be defined in Figma and generated by tokenator because","        \/\/ its value can vary if compact or regular modes.","        \/\/ They can be declared in protocol SizeSemanticTokens,","        \/\/ and defined automaticaly in OUDSTheme+SizeSemanticTokens extension","        var sizeIconWithHeadingXLargeTallMobile: SizeSemanticToken { DimensionRawTokens.dimension650 }","        var sizeIconWithHeadingXLargeTallTablet: SizeSemanticToken { DimensionRawTokens.dimension800 }","","        \/\/ Then the develoment team declares an \"higher\" level size semantic token for sizeIconWithHeadingXLargeTall","        \/\/ inside SizeMultipleSemanticTokens protocol,","        \/\/ and defined inside OUDSTheme+SizeMultipleSemanticTokens extension","        var sizeIconWithHeadingXLargeTall: MultipleSizeSemanticTokens {","            MultipleSizeSemanticTokens(compact: sizeIconWithHeadingXLargeTallMobile, regular: sizeIconWithHeadingXLargeTallTablet)","        }","","        \/\/ If the same value is used whatever the size class is","        var sizeIconWithHeadingXLargeTall: MultipleSizeSemanticTokens { MultipleSizeSemanticTokens(sizeIconWithHeadingXLargeTallTablet) }","","        \/\/ The theme exposes both generated font size semantic tokens and \"crafted\" higher level color semantic tokens.","        \/\/ It is recommended to use the higher level version as it is less error-prone."],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"0.8.0","type":"text"}]}],"style":"note","name":"Since","type":"aside"}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleSizeSemanticTokens"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic"]]},"relationshipsSections":[{"tit